You are here: Home / Faculty: Bert R. BoyceFaculty: Bert R. Boyce





Bert R. Boyce
Professor and Dean Emeritus
Louisiana State University
School of Library and Information Science
lsboyc@lsu.edu




Ph.D, Library and Information Science, Case Western Reserve University
MSLS, Library & Information Science, Case Western Reserve University
BA, History/Political Science, Marietta College
 
Bert Boyce has been an Information System Research Analyst, for the Information Systems Office, at the Library of Congress, a faculty member and acting Dean of the School of Library and Information Science, University of Missouri, Columbia, Missouri, and Dean of the School of Library and Information Science, Louisiana State University, where he is now  Professor and Dean Emeritus. He spent four years as  Editor of the Academic Press Library and Information Science Series. He received the ASIS&T Outstanding Information Science Teacher Award in1989, and has shared the Annual Information Science Book Award from ASIS&T.
 
Selected Publications
Kraft, Donald H. and Bert R. Boyce. Operations Research for Libraries and Information Agencies: Techniques for the Evaluation of Management Decision Alternatives, (San Diego Academic Press, 1991) 193 pages.
Bert R. Boyce, Charles T. Meadow, and Donald H. Kraft. Measurement in Information Science. (San Diego: Academic Press, 1994) 283 pages.
Charles T. Meadow, Bert R. Boyce, and Donald H. Kraft. Text Information Retrieval Systems. 2nd ed. (San Diego: Academic Press, 1999) 364 pages. ASIS 1999 Best Information Science Book Award
Charles T. Meadow, Bert R. Boyce, Donald H. Kraft, Carol L Barry Text Information Retrieval Systems. 3rd ed. (San Diego: Academic Press, 2007) 390 pages.
